gomodel:SYNGO_914  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: Synaptic Neurabin-2/Spinophilin is detected by immuno-EM in spines {Fig2A and E) as well as proximate glial processes (Fig2C). This is quantified in Fig3, no labelling has been observed in synaptic terminals (in contrast to Neurabin-1). Within the spine, Neurabin-2/Spinophilin is located to the PSD and the area in close proximity of the PSD (fig6, quantification in Fig7 and Fig9).. Experimental description: Macaque monkey: \" These experiments were performed on prefrontal cortex (Walker's area 9) obtained from four adult macaque monkeys.\" M&M text" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date          "2017-06-21" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_914" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

